surface lo the Coming War
For the fifth time in its history the United
States is going to war over a principle that
has no foundation in political reality, It is un<
derstandable and perhaps desirable in the Con—
text of the containment policy that the U.S.
should somewhere take a stand against the spending Communist advance. But the point
where the line is drawn should councils with
favorites geographical, political, and military
factors. South Vietnam, with its impenetrable
jungle and profile government, fulfills none of
these basic conditions.
The U,S. should have learned from the
French experience that Vietnam is impossible
to defend. Nationalist guerrillas, striking from
the cover of the population, cannon be detected
by conventional military strategy or superior
military force of numbers. Rather, the instruments of the population that projects the guerrillas must be turned against them. In this,
democraticcapiialisi appeal has been remarkable unsuccessful.
The character of our response to the Communist challenge has actually isolated our own
purposes. By opposite liberal ideas With directories, lightning governments, like that of
Diem, we have enhanced the Communist appeal. One workers whether support of more
liberal governments might have been a more
effective strategy.
By going into Vietnam when the national
government broke down, U.S. policy further
damaged its theoretical appeal by putting
us in a colonial role. At the present time
We control the foreign, military, and economic
policy of Vietnam, if not the government itself.
This has played right into the hands at the
carry—over anti-colonialist statement and die
Communist propaganda attack,
The nature of the Vietnam war further no
cents our homeless position there. Finally receiving we could not defeat the diet long guerrillas in ﬁle south. we have carried the war to
the north with repeated air Strikes. At first
glance this policy may seem reasonable since
our greatest strength is in the air power often
seventh fleet rather than ground forces. How—
ever, we must realize that by expanding the
war in this way, we are visiting reservation by
the columnists using their major strength in
land forces. This could be in the form of a mas-
site invasion of South Vietnam by combined
North Vietnamese and Chinese troops.
We cannon discount the vital interest of
China in the security of North Vietnam. To this
point they have given only indirect assistance
to the diet long, but should U.S. attacks on
the north continue, we can expect them to play
an expanding role. The United States would
not moderate human attacks on Nicaragua even
though we have used that country as a base of
attack on Cuba. Similarly. we must not think
that China will stand by While we attack one of
its wondering countries.
The crucial factor that forecasts the coming
war is the nature of the U,S. commitment. Disregarding the fundamental strategy of always
leaving yourself and your enemy a face-saving
way out, we have essentially closed the door
behind us by staying our practice on victory
in Vietnam.
Thoughts of a associated seeﬂevent at this
point are industry. Our enemy will not go to the
conference table as long as he is winning in the
field and we will not associate from a position
of wellness. '
The Korean example bears out this point.
Negotiations were only possible when the military situation was stalemated, But such a solution is not possible in Vietnam, because the
conflict is not taking place in the Same element.
While we attack the North from the air, our
enemy attacks the South on the ground.
A footnote to this situation is the possibility
that recent defense pleased by Soviet Prime
Minisienifusygin could mean material and tech
local aid in air‘defense to North Vietnam.
This might seriously limit our effectiveness
in the air in addition to investing immediate Soviet interest in 5.13. Asian developments.
A further application of the Vietnam war is
its effect On the division in the Communist blog.
Although We will know more clearly after the
all party congress in March, there is reason in
believe that U.S. estimation of the war has win
en the Chinese and lesbians the common
ground needed to sorted, at least temporarily,
their basic theoretical differences.
in short, going to war (in South Vietnam)
over South Vietnam is not worth the cost, It is
a war we cannon win. If we are going to stand
up to the Communist advance, we should do it
at n time and place Where there are reasonable
chances of success.
