How [he Grinnell College basketball team could lose to St.
Olaf by 17 points and Carleton by 1|) points at Northfleld is a
real power indexed Losses to C02 5053 and Beloit 107-77 only
segment the diploma; and it is everyone' 5 hope of course,
that we will not be shown the answer when these two teams inside party arena this weekend.
The mystery of the Grinnell basketball team began with the
Cornell game, which seemed to prove all pre-season pessimists
wrong. However, any optimistic hopes were displayed just as
quickly with the two disastrous road trips to Northfield and
Cedar Rapids-Beloit,
Thus, last Friday night many students dropped over [0 party hoping they would not want to exit at half-time and head
for Lolita. (Word has it that one person did leave at the half,
but rather than going to the movie he went to the library.)
Instead of being britney, however, the Pioneers extended the
Oles to the suggest.
Again Saturday, thinking Friday night to be an act of God,
students matched back to the gym only to see their heroes root
Carleton 81-65 despite the efforts of a 6" 7" sophomore center
from (of all places!) Crosby—clinton, Minn. The obvious ques<
Lion asked by all was how did this apparent metamorphosis occur? The following is an amateur’s attempt at evaluating the
team and what happened last weekend.
In the past four years we have seen quite a variety of has
ketball player-types here. There has been a guard who could
shoot the eyes out of the basket, but played defense like one of
his feet was failed to the floor; a forward Who could also shoot
well, but tender to trouble the ball off his metatarsals rather
frequently; a center who could rebound and punk, but was not
quite range enough to study his foul shots; and a host of others.
These gentleman were obviously played for their strengths and
in suite of their businesses. BeCause of this, it was easy to become quite exasperated watching their businesses explained
by opposite teams.
This year’s team is somewhat different than these past
teams, however. There is hardly an outstanding shorter, passed
or remainder on the entire team, but they are a group of good
all-around basketball players who don't happen to have a man
over 6' 3” amongst them, Thus, they are forced to work hard
for every basket because they lack the physical strength and talent of most other teams. Last weekend this is precisely what
they did, marketing. driving, and generally out-handling their
opponents.
The encouraging aspect of this turn of events is that the
average Grinnell tan seems to appreciate the effort that is being
put forth by the team. One of the longest cheers or the weekend
occurred after Bob Watt's symbolic theft of the ball from the
hands of St. Olaf's very fine guard Eric Grimsrud.
At home this team is young, exuberant, and aggressive. One
possible explanation for the away games might be that the youth
turns to immaturity, the exuberance to disillusionment, and the
aggressiveness to facility. Without these ingredients in abun—
dance, the team cannon do battle with the detroit-infected square
in the rest of the conference (For the record, these last computational phrases are in just).
